  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Protection of carbon pools and sinks in wetlands and protected areas in Panama</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project provided information and raised awareness on mangrove ecosystems as part of risk management that takes into account climate change - both in reducing the extent of and adapting to the impacts. Mangroves are important and have a multitude of socioeconomic and environmental functions: they serve as carbon stores, protect coastal regions against the effects of climate change and conserve biological diversity. In spite of this, only a few wetlands are effectively protected in Panama. The project supported the management of these protected areas on a total of 13,800 hectares while the national environmental authority provided appropriate training. It also measured the amount of carbon that these ecosystems store.</narrative>
  </description>
